<font size="+2">Job Maintenance Overview - Personnel Plus Website</font>
<br>
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<strong>Login</strong>
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<br>
1.) Enter your username and password then click login.
<br>
2.) Once logged in, you can choose to <strong>Post a New Job</strong> or <strong>Edit Job(s)</strong>.<br>
3.) Click LOGOUT to exit Job Maintenance and to prevent unauthorized access.
<br>
<img src="jpm1.gif" alt="" width="664" height="206" border="0">
<br>
<br>

<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<strong>Posting New Jobs</strong>
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<br>
1.) Type text or perform a cut-and-paste operation for the Job Description.<br>
You can also use basic HTML tags to format the description. For example:
<ul>
<font size="2">
To begin a new paragraph, use this tag - <b>&lt;P&gt;</b><br>
To drop down a line, use - <b>&lt;BR&gt;</b><br>
For text to appear <STRONG>Bold</STRONG>, use - <STRONG>&lt;STRONG&gt; mytext &lt;/STRONG&gt;</STRONG><br>
For text to appear <EM>Italicized</EM> use  - <STRONG>&lt;EM&gt; mytext &lt;/EM&gt;</STRONG><br>
For text to appear <U>Underlined</U> use - <STRONG>&lt;U&gt; mytext &lt;/U&gt;</STRONG><br>
</font>
</ul>
2.) Enter all other required information as needed.<br>
3.) Click <strong>Post Job &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong> when you are ready to save your entry.
<br>
<img src="jpm2.gif" alt="" width="500" height="686" border="0">
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<strong>Editing Jobs</strong>
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<br>
1.) Select your search criteria and click <strong>Search &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong>.
<br>
<img src="jpm3.gif" alt="" width="455" height="359" border="0">
<br>
<br>
2.) Click on a job to edit from the list of search results. Note that jobs marked by a <strong><font color="#ff0000">red  X</font></strong> are closed<br>
and not visible to
the public while <strong><font color="#008000">green-arrow</font></strong> jobs are open and visible.
<br>
<img src="jpm4.gif" alt="" width="654" height="282" border="0">
<br>
<br>
<br>
3.) Make any necessary modifications to and click <strong>Save Changes &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong> when done.
<br>If you want to close the current job position, click the CLOSE JOB link-- you can always reopen a closed<br> job by clicking the REOPEN JOB link from the Edit Job Posting form.
<br>
<img src="jpm5.gif" alt="" width="644" height="764" border="0">
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<strong>Tips & Tricks</strong>
<hr width="660" align="left" size="1">
<br>
<li>You can avoid having to entirely re-key multiple job listings that are similar. To do this, type in your first job order, click <strong>Post Job &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong>, then, click the BACK button on your browser until you are back at your first job order form again (usually only 1 click is required). Make changes to the Job Title, etc., and click <strong>Post Job &gt;&gt;&gt;</strong> to save it. Repeat as many times as needed. </li><br>
<li>Enter job postings ahead of time: Post a Job as usual then use CLOSE JOB from the Edit Job(s) option. When you want the job visible to the public, use the REOPEN JOB option.</li>
<br>
<li>If you navigate away from the Maintenance Options they can always be found by returning to the Home Page again.</li>


